London Edmund Wanner
Sr. I never had the honnour before to write to you for want of occasion, these to
advise you that m. marco ant. mischino di genua hath sent a packett of point
laces to colonia to m. Ruysten & van boom to follow my order, they
beeng for yd acctt. & order wherefore desire to know, how you please to have
expediated the said packett, the valew of the contents, & number & marck
of the packett which m. mischino omitted & you may assure yd self, that
Ill do all possible endeavours to serve you to content: besides in case you
are accquainted in our flanders lace trade, I can serve you here in buying &
sending to you for I make itt much mij bussynes & have hetherto found my
commissions to increase where by I finde the satisfaction, of what I send to
give content to my freinds, so in case I can serve you in that, or any other
trade freely command
